 {"id":"bd-0zvn","title":"[Conformance] Implement Runtime Fundamentals Test Suite","description":"## Overview

Implement the Runtime Fundamentals conformance test suite covering task spawning, cancellation, joining, timeouts, and select/race semantics.

## Rationale

These tests validate the core async runtime behavior that everything else depends on. If these fail, nothing works correctly.

## Test Cases

### RT-001: Basic Task Spawn and Join

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-001",
    name: "Basic spawn and join",
    description: "Spawn a simple task and await its completion",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["spawn", "join", "basic"],
    expected: "Task completes with returned value",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let handle = rt.spawn(async { 42i32 });
            let result = handle.await;

            checkpoint("task_completed", json!({"result": result}));

            assert_eq!(result, 42, "Task should return spawned value");
            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-002: Multiple Concurrent Tasks

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-002",
    name: "Multiple concurrent tasks",
    description: "Spawn multiple tasks that run concurrently",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["spawn", "concurrent"],
    expected: "All tasks complete with correct values",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let handles: Vec<_> = (0..100)
                .map(|i| rt.spawn(async move { i * 2 }))
                .collect();

            checkpoint("all_spawned", json!({"count": handles.len()}));

            let results: Vec<_> = join_all(handles).await;

            checkpoint("all_joined", json!({"count": results.len()}));

            let expected: Vec<_> = (0..100).map(|i| i * 2).collect();
            assert_eq!(results, expected, "All tasks should return doubled values");

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-003: Task Cancellation via Abort

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-003",
    name: "Task cancellation via abort",
    description: "Abort a running task before it completes",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["spawn", "cancel", "abort"],
    expected: "Task is cancelled, does not complete its work",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let completed = Arc::new(AtomicBool::new(false));
            let completed_clone = completed.clone();

            let handle = rt.spawn(async move {
                rt.sleep(Duration::from_secs(10)).await;
                completed_clone.store(true, Ordering::SeqCst);
            });

            // Give task time to start
            rt.sleep(Duration::from_millis(10)).await;
            checkpoint("task_started", json!({}));

            // Abort it
            handle.abort();
            checkpoint("abort_called", json!({}));

            // Wait a bit to ensure it had time to complete if not cancelled
            rt.sleep(Duration::from_millis(50)).await;

            assert!(
                !completed.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
                "Cancelled task should not complete"
            );

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-004: Join Handle Drop Does Not Cancel

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-004",
    name: "Dropping JoinHandle does not cancel task",
    description: "Task continues running after JoinHandle is dropped",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["spawn", "detach"],
    expected: "Task completes even without awaiting handle",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let completed = Arc::new(AtomicBool::new(false));
            let completed_clone = completed.clone();

            {
                let _handle = rt.spawn(async move {
                    rt.sleep(Duration::from_millis(10)).await;
                    completed_clone.store(true, Ordering::SeqCst);
                });
                // Handle dropped here
            }

            checkpoint("handle_dropped", json!({}));

            // Wait for task to complete
            rt.sleep(Duration::from_millis(50)).await;

            assert!(
                completed.load(Ordering::SeqCst),
                "Task should complete even after handle dropped"
            );

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-005: Timeout Success (Future Completes in Time)

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-005",
    name: "Timeout with fast future",
    description: "Timeout wrapping a future that completes before deadline",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["timeout", "success"],
    expected: "Returns Ok with the future's result",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let result = rt.timeout(
                Duration::from_secs(1),
                async { 42 }
            ).await;

            checkpoint("timeout_completed", json!({"result": format!("{:?}", result)}));

            assert!(result.is_ok(), "Fast future should not timeout");
            assert_eq!(result.unwrap(), 42);

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-006: Timeout Expiration

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-006",
    name: "Timeout expiration",
    description: "Timeout wrapping a future that exceeds deadline",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["timeout", "expiration"],
    expected: "Returns Err(Elapsed) after deadline",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let start = Instant::now();

            let result = rt.timeout(
                Duration::from_millis(50),
                async {
                    rt.sleep(Duration::from_secs(10)).await;
                    42
                }
            ).await;

            let elapsed = start.elapsed();
            checkpoint("timeout_elapsed", json!({
                "elapsed_ms": elapsed.as_millis(),
                "result": format!("{:?}", result)
            }));

            assert!(result.is_err(), "Slow future should timeout");
            assert!(
                elapsed < Duration::from_millis(200),
                "Should timeout quickly, not wait for inner future"
            );

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-007: Select/Race First Wins

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-007",
    name: "Select first completer wins",
    description: "Racing two futures, faster one wins",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["select", "race"],
    expected: "Returns result of faster future",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let fast = async {
                rt.sleep(Duration::from_millis(10)).await;
                "fast"
            };
            let slow = async {
                rt.sleep(Duration::from_secs(10)).await;
                "slow"
            };

            let start = Instant::now();
            let winner = select(fast, slow).await;
            let elapsed = start.elapsed();

            checkpoint("race_completed", json!({
                "winner": winner,
                "elapsed_ms": elapsed.as_millis()
            }));

            assert_eq!(winner, "fast", "Fast future should win");
            assert!(
                elapsed < Duration::from_millis(100),
                "Should complete quickly"
            );

            TestResult::passed()
        })
    }
}
```

### RT-008: Nested Spawns

```rust
conformance_test! {
    id: "rt-008",
    name: "Nested task spawning",
    description: "Tasks spawning other tasks",
    category: TestCategory::Runtime,
    tags: ["spawn", "nested"],
    expected: "All nested tasks complete correctly",
    test: |rt| {
        rt.block_on(async {
            let handle = rt.spawn(async {
                let inner = rt.spawn(async {
                    rt.spawn(async { 1 }).await +
                    rt.spawn(async { 2 }).await
                });
                inner.await + rt.spawn(async { 3 }).await
            });

            let result = handle.await;
            checkpoint("nested_completed", json!({"result": result}));

            assert_eq!(result, 6, "1 + 2 + 3 = 6");
